# One Electrical Object -- deliberately the plainest patch in this
# repo: pure sine, zero detune, zero chorus, zero LFO, zero automation
# anywhere in the song that uses it. Every one of its five identical
# instances commands the exact same note through the exact same
# numbers. Whatever difference you hear between them is not something
# I wrote -- it's voct_error, common_drift, and the shared rail/heat
# substrate doing what they do to any two "identical" boards on one
# chassis, audible with nothing else in the way.
waveform 0
osc2_wave 0
osc2_pitch 0
osc2_level 0
osc3_wave 0
osc3_pitch 0
osc3_level 0
detune 0
sub 0
circuit 0
key_track 0.2
osc_fm 0
sync 0
ring 0
glide 0
pulse_width 0.5
attack 1.8
decay 0.5
sustain 0.95
release 2.0
filter_env 0
filter_attack 0.5
filter_decay 0.5
filter_sustain 0.5
filter_release 0.5
cutoff 6000
resonance 0
drive 1.0
saturation 0.3
hpf 16
